How many hours
to sleep before school?

17:23.334 --> 17:24.334
Two and a half.

17:24.334 --> 17:25.834
Ohh.

17:25.834 --> 17:29.000
Well, at least I only
have to stay awake
for one class.

17:29.000 --> 17:30.200
Yeah. Me, too.

17:32.100 --> 17:33.167
Let's go.

17:33.167 --> 17:34.634
Ugh.
Uhh!

17:42.767 --> 17:44.901
I can't sleep with
that damn woman in my bed.

17:49.701 --> 17:51.100
God,
I'm starving.

17:54.501 --> 17:56.000
Never anything
in the fridge.

18:17.501 --> 18:19.367
[CRYING]

18:34.534 --> 18:36.000
Oh, God.

18:36.000 --> 18:38.801
Seven-thirty in the morning,
and I'm up.

18:38.801 --> 18:41.100
This is inhuman.

18:41.100 --> 18:43.200
Gee, maybe Mommy
will make us breakfast.

18:44.601 --> 18:46.367
Oh.

18:46.367 --> 18:47.567
That's me.

18:50.434 --> 18:51.934
Oh, no.

18:53.868 --> 18:55.067
He didn't.

19:02.767 --> 19:04.300
Yep.
He did.

19:05.501 --> 19:07.567
Wake up,
you moron.

19:07.567 --> 19:09.834
You ate
my final exam.

19:09.834 --> 19:10.834
Naah.

19:10.834 --> 19:12.467
Ugh.

19:12.467 --> 19:14.300
You didn't eat
my Jell-O, did you,
Daddy?

19:14.300 --> 19:16.167
[SNORING]

19:17.901 --> 19:19.367
It's all right,
honey. It's here.

19:19.367 --> 19:21.300
Oh,
thank God.

19:21.300 --> 19:22.767
Well, what are you
gonna do, Mom?

19:22.767 --> 19:24.701
I don't know.

19:24.701 --> 19:27.067
There's not time
to make another one.

19:27.067 --> 19:29.033
Maybe Miss Beyer
will understand.

19:32.567 --> 19:35.000
I don't want to be
dumber than the dog.

19:37.334 --> 19:38.501
Oh, well.

19:38.501 --> 19:40.400
It's just a stupid
piece of paper.

19:40.400 --> 19:41.634
Who needs a diploma?

19:41.634 --> 19:43.834
Means nothing at all.

19:43.834 --> 19:46.868
I'll just go there...
and face the music.

19:50.334 --> 19:51.767
[BURPS]

19:53.067 --> 19:54.701
Nice. B+.

19:56.234 --> 19:58.601
Ruben. A+.

20:00.667 --> 20:02.534
Ah, Miss Wanker.
Your card, please.

20:02.534 --> 20:04.167
Oh.

20:05.567 --> 20:06.801
"Jell-O."

20:08.367 --> 20:10.701
Excellent. A-.

20:10.701 --> 20:12.267
Oh, ha-ha!

20:12.267 --> 20:13.901
Hey, ma.

20:13.901 --> 20:15.701
Miss Bundy,
your card.

20:15.701 --> 20:17.334
Oh. I have one
for her.

20:18.868 --> 20:20.501
"Crowned rack
of lamb."

20:23.234 --> 20:24.901
Hey.

20:26.400 --> 20:28.100
Hey!

20:30.701 --> 20:34.133
Oh, Kelly...this is
the happiest moment
of my life.

20:34.133 --> 20:36.400
I finally got a diploma.
Ha-ha.

20:36.400 --> 20:39.467
I'm so glad you're here
to share this moment with me.

20:39.467 --> 20:41.400
Yeah, mom, I'll
remember it fondly

20:41.400 --> 20:43.868
while I'm sweating
through summer school.

20:43.868 --> 20:45.367
Why did you do it, Mom?

20:45.367 --> 20:47.267
Why did you
take my Jell-O?

20:48.601 --> 20:51.534
Oh, honey, don't you
understand?

20:51.534 --> 20:53.901
I did it for you.

20:53.901 --> 20:58.467
Sweetie, this is your
last summer as
my little girl.

20:58.467 --> 20:59.767
Now, if I'd
let you graduate,

20:59.767 --> 21:01.133
your father would
have you work

21:01.133 --> 21:02.767
the whole summer.

21:02.767 --> 21:07.467
That would mean no beach,
no shopping...no vandalizing.

21:08.868 --> 21:11.834
This way...all
you have to do is

21:11.834 --> 21:13.667
spend one hour
a day in class,

21:13.667 --> 21:18.267
and the rest of the time...
is summertime.

21:18.267 --> 21:19.834
So, Kelly,
just think of this

21:19.834 --> 21:22.200
as my graduation
present to you.

21:22.200 --> 21:24.601
Oh, thank you, Mom.

21:24.601 --> 21:26.567
You're the best.
Ha-ha.

21:31.200 --> 21:33.467
Come on, it's time for
graduation pictures.

21:33.467 --> 21:34.634
Oops.
Got to go.

21:34.634 --> 21:36.133
Okay.

21:36.133 --> 21:39.334
Oh, man. I'm gonna
go to school
during the summer.

21:43.801 --> 21:44.901
Hey.

21:45.968 --> 21:47.501
Hey!

22:02.801 --> 22:05.000
